  "doc_id": "15275",
  "text": "We implemented CRsAE on Keras with TensorFlow as a backend and trained it on a GPU (NVIDIA Tesla V100) provided by AWS. The number of trainable parameters is K ×C +1. We used the ADAM optimizer [CITATION_1] to solve for the parameters by mini-batch gradient descent where the gradients are computed using the back-propagation algorithms described in the previous section. For faster convergence, we used the AMSGrad variant of ADAM [CITATION_2] . The learned parameters are the ones minimizing the validation loss over all epochs. Gamma Hyper-prior Parameters: Given a dense dictionary, a suggested value for the regularization parameter motivated by theory [CITATION_3] is λ = √ 2 log(C×Ne) σ",
